Transferred from the Adobe Open Source Subversion Repository
canCancelBackKeyBehavior has been renamed exitApplicationOnBackKey (also impacts ViewNavigator and TabbedViewNavigator)
backKeyHandler method is now mx_internal, it is no longer part of public api
useDefaultTransitions property has been removed from the framework
canRemoveCurrentView is now mx_internal, it is no longer part of the public api
createVisibiliyAnimation() method has been removed and replaced with the createActionBarShowEffect() and createActionBarHideEffect() methods.
commitViewChange, beginViewChanged and endViewChanged have been renamed to commitNavigatorAction, committingNavigatorAction and navigatorActionCommitted.
maintainNavigationStack removed from ViewNavigator and moved to TabbedViewNavigator
VIEW_ACTIVATE, VIEW_DEACTIVATE and REMOVING have been removed from the FlexEvent class and added to the new ViewNavigatorEvent class.
ViewNavigatorEvent class now has a "action" property that indicates what the last committed navigation operation was
ViewNavigatorAction enum class added and is used to populate the action property of a ViewNavigatorEvent

View now dispatches a "backKeyPressed" (FlexEvent.BACK_KEY_PRESSED) event when the back device key is pressed.  This is a cancelable event.  When cancelled, the MobileApplication's default back behavior will not run.
Added a maintainNavigationStack property to the view navigator.  When false, the navigation stack of a navigator is cleared when deactivated.
Added maintainNavigationStack proxy property to the application
